Male genitalia
(genital preparation № OG–065-2018) (
Figs 27–28
). Unfortunately, the species of the genus have almost identical male genitalia. Very slight differences can be found in the valva and saccus shapes. In addition, there are several differences in the length and thickness of the aedeagus (cp. 
Figs 27–32
).
